text: Frenelles-en-Vexin is a commune in the Eure department in Normandy in northern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Boisemont (the seat), Corny and Fresne-l'Archevêque.Arrêté préfectoral 27 November 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Eure department ==References== Category:Communes of Eure
title: Frenelles-en-Vexin
